ext in which major components of the criminal justice system evolved: material on the history of crime and deviance, juvenile delinquency, and reform movements. The third chapter covers the history and developmetn of the criminal law and the criminal courts. Finally, chapter four deals with documents relating to the development of institutions for coping with criminals, the poor, and the insane; punishment and treatment of incarcerated offenders; penal reform; and the history and development of various sentencing alternatives, such as transportation, probation, and parole. Author and subject indexes provide ready access to the bibliography, and an appendix of sources searched is of invaluable assistance to researchers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCorrectional institutionszCanadaxHistoryvBibliography. 0aCrimezCanadaxHistoryvBibliography. 0aCriminal justice, Administration ofzCanadaxHistoryvBibliography. 0aCriminal lawzCanadaxHistoryvBibliography. 0aPolicezCanadaxHistoryvBibliography. 0aPublic welfarezCanadaxHistoryvBibliography. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aJ. Cox, Sandra, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aJ. Matthews, Catherine, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148758467240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487584672423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487584672.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE